<div type="definition">
<p>POSSIBLE AND IF TRIED OFTEN ACHIEVED LACKING:without EFFORT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for easiness of actions is yì 易 (ant. nán 難 "difficult").</p>
<p>2. Qīng 輕 "light" is sometimes used to effortlessness of every kind.</p>
<p>3. Líng 泠 is a poetic word referring to graceful effortless ease of movement.</p>
        </div>
